  "prompt": "Where do I start when looking for colleges?",
  "response": "Here are some steps to help you start your college search:\n\n1. Self-Assessment\n- Consider your interests and career goals\n- Evaluate your academic strengths\n- Determine your preferred learning environment\n\n2. Research Factors\n- Academic programs\n- Location\n- Size of school\n- Cost and financial aid\n- Campus culture\n- Admission requirements\n\n3. Practical Resources\n- High school guidance counselor\n- College websites\n- College search websites (like College Board, Niche)\n- College fairs\n- College guidebooks\n\n4. Explore Different Types of Colleges\n- 4-year universities\n- Community colleges\n- Liberal arts colleges\n- Technical/vocational schools\n- Public vs. private institutions\n\n5. Create a List\n- Safety schools\n- Target schools\n- Reach schools\n\n6. Visit Campuses\n- Attend information sessions\n- Take campus tours\n- Talk to current students\n- Sit in on classes if possible\n\n7. Prepare for Application Process\n- Take standardized tests (SAT/ACT)\n- Gather recommendation letters\n- Write application essays\n- Meet application deadlines\n\nStart early and be systematic in your approach.",
